This is a Vigenere cipher.

=======================================================================
SOLUTION
=======================================================================

Codeword : TRAJAN
Key      : SCUBA  (length 5)
Language : French

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Source text
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
"L'Albatros" by Charles Baudelaire, from Les Fleurs du Mal (1857).
The ciphertext encodes the poem in its entirety, with a codeword
message appended immediately before the final line:

  "LE MOT POUR ETAGE QUATRE EST TRAJAN"
  ("The word for stage four is TRAJAN")

TRAJAN (Marcus Ulpius Traianus) was Roman Emperor AD 98-117.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Methodology
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

1.  STRIP & COUNT
    The ciphertext (604 uppercase letters, formatted as 23-letter
    rows separated by blank lines) was stripped to a flat string of
    604 A-Z characters.

2.  INDEX OF COINCIDENCE (IOC)
    For key lengths 1-30, the ciphertext was split into kl independent
    Caesar streams and the mean IOC computed.  IOC peaks clearly at
    key lengths that are multiples of 5:

      kl=5  IOC=0.0786   <<<  true key length
      kl=10 IOC=0.0788
      kl=20 IOC=0.0791

    French plain text has IOC ≈ 0.078, consistent with the peaks.
    All non-multiple-of-5 lengths show IOC ≈ 0.044 (near random).

3.  KASISKI TEST
    Repeated trigram spacings also strongly favor kl=5 (59 votes),
    with kl=10 and kl=20 as harmonics.

4.  KEY RECOVERY (Chi-squared)
    For each of the 5 streams, all 26 Caesar shifts were tried and
    scored by Pearson Chi-squared against English and French letter
    frequencies.  The shift minimizing Chi-squared recovers one key
    character.  Result:  K-E-Y = S-C-U-B-A

5.  QUADGRAM SCORING
    The French quadgram table scored the decryption highest
    (-2504.8), confirming the language and key.

